  <title translate="true">SYS(8013) - Change system time</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">SYS(8013) - Change system time</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Changes the system local date and time</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Inline heading"><text styleclass="Inline heading" translate="true">Syntax</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">SYS( 8013, tTime )</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Inline heading"><text styleclass="Inline heading" translate="true">Parameters</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Parameter"><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">tTime</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Explanation"><text styleclass="Explanation" translate="true">New time. The time must be expressed as local time. Time zone and daylight saving time information are not changed. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Inline heading"><text styleclass="Inline heading" translate="true">Remarks</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Changing the date and time might require elevated privileges. SYS(8013) fails silently if the current user doesn&apos;t have the permissions to change the system clock.</text></para>
